"{\"uid\": \"myrepublica.nagariknetwork.com-news-olympia-dukakis-oscar-winning-moonstruck-actress-dies-at-89\", \"entities\": [{\"sentence\": \"Subscribe Now  Olympia Dukakis, who won an Oscar for her performance as a sardonic, middle-aged mother who advises her headstrong daughter on matters of love in the 1987 romantic film comedy \\\"Moonstruck,\\\" died on Saturday at age 89.\", \"from\": 0, \"to\": 232, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 15, \"end\": 30, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Olympia_Dukakis\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Olympia Dukakis\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Olympia_Dukakis\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Olympia_Dukakis\"}, {\"begin\": 43, \"end\": 48, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Academy_Awards\", \"score\": 0.9999615123286955, \"rank\": 3.8418226011099054e-05, \"text\": \"Oscar\", \"types\": [\"Q618779\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Academy_Awards\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Academy_Awards\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Dukakis - a cousin of unsuccessful 1988 Democratic U.S. presidential nominee Michael Dukakis - passed away at her New York City home on Saturday morning after months of failing health, according to her agent, Allison Levy.\", \"from\": 234, \"to\": 456, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 274, \"end\": 284, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/California_Democratic_Party\", \"score\": 0.999524999433783, \"rank\": 0.0004727200884236897, \"text\": \"Democratic\", \"types\": [\"Q7278\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/California_Democratic_Party\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/California_Democratic_Party\"}, {\"begin\": 311, \"end\": 326, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Michael_Dukakis\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Michael Dukakis\", \"types\": [\"Q82955\", \"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Michael_Dukakis\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Michael_Dukakis\"}, {\"begin\": 443, \"end\": 450, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Davey_Allison\", \"score\": 0.985211952303995, \"rank\": 0.014944751308708273, \"text\": \"Allison\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q378622\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Davey_Allison\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Davey_Allison\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Her daughter, Christina Zorich, was by her side.\", \"from\": 457, \"to\": 505, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 471, \"end\": 480, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Christina_Aguilera\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 6.62671519013675e-20, \"text\": \"Christina\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Christina_Aguilera\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Christina_Aguilera\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Dukakis, the Massachusetts-born daughter of Greek immigrants, worked for decades as a stage, TV and film actor before rocketing to fame at age 56 playing the mother of Cher's character in \\\"Moonstruck.\\\"\", \"from\": 507, \"to\": 708, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 551, \"end\": 556, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Greek_language\", \"score\": 0.8291652258764567, \"rank\": 0.12784420973307892, \"text\": \"Greek\", \"types\": [\"Q315\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Greek_language\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Greek_language\"}, {\"begin\": 675, \"end\": 679, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Cher\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 2.4732115435591103e-56, \"text\": \"Cher\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Cher\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Cher\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Dukakis built on that with roles in films including \\\"Look Who's Talking\\\" (1989) and its sequels with John Travolta and Kirstie Alley, \\\"Steel Magnolias\\\" (1989) with Shirley MacLaine, Sally Field and Julia Roberts, director Woody Allen's \\\"Mighty Aphrodite\\\" (1995) and \\\"Mr. Holland's Opus\\\" (1995) with Richard Dreyfuss.\", \"from\": 710, \"to\": 1026, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 811, \"end\": 824, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/John_Travolta\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"John Travolta\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/John_Travolta\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/John_Travolta\"}, {\"begin\": 829, \"end\": 842, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kirstie_Alley\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Kirstie Alley\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kirstie_Alley\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kirstie_Alley\"}, {\"begin\": 874, \"end\": 890, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Shirley_MacLaine\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Shirley MacLaine\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Shirley_MacLaine\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Shirley_MacLaine\"}, {\"begin\": 892, \"end\": 903, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sally_Field\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Sally Field\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sally_Field\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sally_Field\"}, {\"begin\": 908, \"end\": 921, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Julia_Roberts\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 2.841762760717122e-69, \"text\": \"Julia Roberts\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Julia_Roberts\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Julia_Roberts\"}, {\"begin\": 932, \"end\": 943, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Woody_Allen\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 3.8948502678982304e-66, \"text\": \"Woody Allen\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Woody_Allen\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Woody_Allen\"}, {\"begin\": 981, \"end\": 988, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Netherlands\", \"score\": 0.6022872967677435, \"rank\": 0.6603365961389674, \"text\": \"Holland\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Netherlands\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Netherlands\"}, {\"begin\": 1009, \"end\": 1025, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Richard_Dreyfuss\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Richard Dreyfuss\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Richard_Dreyfuss\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Richard_Dreyfuss\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Dukakis, a master of deadpan humor, also was nominated for Emmy awards for TV roles in 1991, 1998 and 1999.\", \"from\": 1028, \"to\": 1135, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1049, \"end\": 1062, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Deadpan\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"deadpan humor\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Deadpan\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Deadpan\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"In the 1970s, she co-founded the Whole Theater in the New York City suburb of Montclair, New Jersey, after moving there with her husband, fellow actor Louis Zorich.\", \"from\": 1136, \"to\": 1300, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1169, \"end\": 1174, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Committee_of_the_whole\", \"score\": 0.9999998529238036, \"rank\": 1.4707628265380157e-07, \"text\": \"Whole\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Committee_of_the_whole\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Committee_of_the_whole\"}, {\"begin\": 1190, \"end\": 1203, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/New_York_City\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 2.131474969382998e-25, \"text\": \"New York City\", \"types\": [\"Q515\", \"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/New_York_City\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/New_York_City\"}, {\"begin\": 1225, \"end\": 1235, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/New_Jersey\", \"score\": 0.9999999933970685, \"rank\": 6.55244541883133e-09, \"text\": \"New Jersey\", \"types\": [\"Q3455524\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/New_Jersey\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/New_Jersey\"}, {\"begin\": 1287, \"end\": 1299, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Louis_Zorich\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Louis Zorich\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Louis_Zorich\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Louis_Zorich\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"But, for many, her most indelible performance came in director Norman Jewison's \\\"Moonstruck\\\" as Rose Castorini, a Brooklyn woman with a cheating plumber husband (Vincent Gardenia) and a widowed bookkeeper daughter, Loretta (Cher), who has an affair with her fiance's opera-buff brother (Nicolas Cage).\", \"from\": 1302, \"to\": 1603, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1365, \"end\": 1379, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Norman_Jewison\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Norman Jewison\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Norman_Jewison\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Norman_Jewison\"}, {\"begin\": 1398, \"end\": 1402, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Rose_Tyler\", \"score\": 0.9802833550717579, \"rank\": 0.020112692577031556, \"text\": \"Rose\", \"types\": [\"Q95074\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Rose_Tyler\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Rose_Tyler\"}, {\"begin\": 1416, \"end\": 1424, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Brooklyn\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.4505189150930348e-16, \"text\": \"Brooklyn\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Brooklyn\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Brooklyn\"}, {\"begin\": 1464, \"end\": 1480, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Vincent_Gardenia\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Vincent Gardenia\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Vincent_Gardenia\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Vincent_Gardenia\"}, {\"begin\": 1526, \"end\": 1530, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Cher\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 2.4732115435591103e-56, \"text\": \"Cher\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Cher\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Cher\"}, {\"begin\": 1589, \"end\": 1601, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Nicolas_Cage\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Nicolas Cage\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Nicolas_Cage\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Nicolas_Cage\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Her banter with Cher was among the film's highlights, including a scene in which Dukakis scolded her daughter during a kitchen dissection of her love life.\", \"from\": 1605, \"to\": 1760, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1621, \"end\": 1625, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Cher\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 2.4732115435591103e-56, \"text\": \"Cher\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Cher\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Cher\"}, {\"begin\": 1686, \"end\": 1693, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Michael_Dukakis\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Dukakis\", \"types\": [\"Q82955\", \"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Michael_Dukakis\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Michael_Dukakis\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"Your life's going down the toilet,\\\" Dukakis said in her throaty voice.\", \"from\": 1762, \"to\": 1833, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1799, \"end\": 1806, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Michael_Dukakis\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Dukakis\", \"types\": [\"Q82955\", \"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Michael_Dukakis\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Michael_Dukakis\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"At another point, she tells Cher it is good she did not love her fiance.\", \"from\": 1834, \"to\": 1906, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1862, \"end\": 1866, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Cher\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 2.4732115435591103e-56, \"text\": \"Cher\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Cher\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Cher\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"When you love them, they drive you crazy because they know they can.\\\"\", \"from\": 1907, \"to\": 1977, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"Olympia Dukakis Was An Amazing, Academy Award Winning Actress,\\\" actress and singer Cher wrote on Twitter.\", \"from\": 1979, \"to\": 2085, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2063, \"end\": 2067, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Cher\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 2.4732115435591103e-56, \"text\": \"Cher\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Cher\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Cher\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"...\", \"from\": 2086, \"to\": 2090, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"I talked to her 3Wks Ago.\", \"from\": 2091, \"to\": 2116, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Rip Dear One.\\\"\", \"from\": 2117, \"to\": 2131, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Another Oscar winner, Viola Davis, called Dukakis \\\"the consummate actress\\\" on Twitter.\", \"from\": 2132, \"to\": 2218, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2140, \"end\": 2145, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Academy_Awards\", \"score\": 0.9999615123286955, \"rank\": 3.8418226011099054e-05, \"text\": \"Oscar\", \"types\": [\"Q618779\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Academy_Awards\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Academy_Awards\"}, {\"begin\": 2154, \"end\": 2165, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Viola_Davis\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Viola Davis\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Viola_Davis\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Viola_Davis\"}, {\"begin\": 2174, \"end\": 2181, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Michael_Dukakis\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Dukakis\", \"types\": [\"Q82955\", \"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Michael_Dukakis\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Michael_Dukakis\"}, {\"begin\": 2210, \"end\": 2217, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Twitter\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 9.716193484865329e-20, \"text\": \"Twitter\", \"types\": [\"Q386724\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Twitter\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Twitter\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"You made all around you step up their game.\", \"from\": 2219, \"to\": 2263, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"A joy to work with.\", \"from\": 2264, \"to\": 2283, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Rest well.\\\"\", \"from\": 2284, \"to\": 2295, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"Moonstruck,\\\" considered one of Hollywood's great romantic comedies, won three Academy Awards, including Cher as best actress, and was nominated in three other categories, including best picture.\", \"from\": 2297, \"to\": 2492, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2329, \"end\": 2338, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Cinema_of_the_United_States\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 2.2295881700146924e-19, \"text\": \"Hollywood\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Cinema_of_the_United_States\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Cinema_of_the_United_States\"}, {\"begin\": 2402, \"end\": 2406, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Cher\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 2.4732115435591103e-56, \"text\": \"Cher\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Cher\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Cher\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"It also was one of the highest-grossing films of 1987.\", \"from\": 2493, \"to\": 2547, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"In accepting her Oscar as best supporting actress in April 1988, when her cousin was battling to become the Democratic Party's presidential nominee, she thanked Jewison, her husband and a few others.\", \"from\": 2549, \"to\": 2748, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2566, \"end\": 2571, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Academy_Awards\", \"score\": 0.9999615123286955, \"rank\": 3.8418226011099054e-05, \"text\": \"Oscar\", \"types\": [\"Q618779\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Academy_Awards\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Academy_Awards\"}, {\"begin\": 2657, \"end\": 2673, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Democratic_Party_of_Korea\", \"score\": 0.6004982586778382, \"rank\": 0.6652837631896378, \"text\": \"Democratic Party\", \"types\": [\"Q7278\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Democratic_Party_of_Korea\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Democratic_Party_of_Korea\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"She then raised the golden statuette over her head and shouted to the worldwide TV audience, \\\"OK, Michael, let us go.\\\"\", \"from\": 2749, \"to\": 2867, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Michael Dukakis won the nomination but the Massachusetts governor lost badly in the general election to Republican Vice President George H.W.\", \"from\": 2869, \"to\": 3010, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2869, \"end\": 2884, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Michael_Dukakis\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Michael Dukakis\", \"types\": [\"Q82955\", \"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Michael_Dukakis\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Michael_Dukakis\"}, {\"begin\": 2912, \"end\": 2925, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Massachusetts\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 6.698045127355388e-15, \"text\": \"Massachusetts\", \"types\": [\"Q3455524\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Massachusetts\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Massachusetts\"}, {\"begin\": 2973, \"end\": 2983, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/California_Republican_Party\", \"score\": 0.9790692549814833, \"rank\": 0.02137502562564885, \"text\": \"Republican\", \"types\": [\"Q7278\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/California_Republican_Party\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/California_Republican_Party\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Bush.\", \"from\": 3011, \"to\": 3016, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3011, \"end\": 3015, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/George_W._Bush\", \"score\": 0.621298261161586, \"rank\": 0.6095329127908771, \"text\": \"Bush\", \"types\": [\"Q82955\", \"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/George_W._Bush\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/George_W._Bush\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Like her cousin, Olympia Dukakis embraced liberal views, advocating for causes including women's rights, gay rights and the environment.\", \"from\": 3017, \"to\": 3153, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3034, \"end\": 3049, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Olympia_Dukakis\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Olympia Dukakis\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Olympia_Dukakis\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Olympia_Dukakis\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"She had an incredible life and we were very proud of her,\\\" Michael Dukakis told the Boston Globe on Saturday.\", \"from\": 3155, \"to\": 3265, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3215, \"end\": 3230, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Michael_Dukakis\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Michael Dukakis\", \"types\": [\"Q82955\", \"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Michael_Dukakis\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Michael_Dukakis\"}, {\"begin\": 3240, \"end\": 3246, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Boston\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 2.616654599468077e-14, \"text\": \"Boston\", \"types\": [\"Q515\", \"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Boston\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Boston\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Olympia Dukakis was born in Lowell, Massachusetts, on June 20, 1931 and continued to act into her 80s.\", \"from\": 3266, \"to\": 3368, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3266, \"end\": 3281, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Olympia_Dukakis\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Olympia Dukakis\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Olympia_Dukakis\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Olympia_Dukakis\"}, {\"begin\": 3294, \"end\": 3315, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Lowell,_Massachusetts\", \"score\": 0.9999867923233084, \"rank\": 1.3207851407268071e-05, \"text\": \"Lowell, Massachusetts\", \"types\": [\"Q515\", \"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Lowell,_Massachusetts\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Lowell,_Massachusetts\"}, {\"begin\": 3294, \"end\": 3315, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Lowell,_Massachusetts\", \"score\": 0.9999867923233084, \"rank\": 1.3207851407268071e-05, \"text\": \"Lowell, Massachusetts\", \"types\": [\"Q515\", \"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Lowell,_Massachusetts\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resourc